<p>

<b>Hindu texts</b> are manuscripts and historical literature related to any of the diverse traditions within <a href="/wiki/Hinduism" title="Hinduism">Hinduism</a>. A few texts are shared resources across these traditions and broadly considered as Hindu scriptures.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-goodallix_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-goodallix-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> These include the <a href="/wiki/Veda" class="mw-redirect" title="Veda">Vedas</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Upanishad" class="mw-redirect" title="Upanishad">Upanishads</a>. Scholars hesitate in defining the term "Hindu scripture" given the diverse nature of <a href="/wiki/Hinduism" title="Hinduism">Hinduism</a>,<sup id="cite_ref-goodallix_2-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-goodallix-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-klausscrip_3-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-klausscrip-3">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> many include <a href="/wiki/Bhagavad_Gita" title="Bhagavad Gita">Bhagavad Gita</a> and <a href="/wiki/%C4%80gama_(Hinduism)" class="mw-redirect" title="Āgama (Hinduism)">Agamas</a> as Hindu scriptures,<sup id="cite_ref-goodallix_2-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-goodallix-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-klausscrip_3-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-klausscrip-3">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> while Dominic Goodall includes <a href="/wiki/Bhagavata_Purana" title="Bhagavata Purana">Bhagavata Purana</a> and <a href="/wiki/Yajnavalkya_Smriti" class="mw-redirect" title="Yajnavalkya Smriti">Yajnavalkya Smriti</a> to the list of Hindu scriptures.<sup id="cite_ref-goodallix_2-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-goodallix-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<div id="toc" class="toc" role="navigation" aria-labelledby="mw-toc-heading"><input type="checkbox" role="button" id="toctogglecheckbox" class="toctogglecheckbox" style="display:none" /><div class="toctitle" lang="en" dir="ltr"><h2 id="mw-toc-heading">Contents</h2><span class="toctogglespan"><label class="toctogglelabel" for="toctogglecheckbox"></label></span></div>
